          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Emerging Mathematical Ideas</strong></p>",
            "<p>Explore enlarging a geometric figure using “rep-tiling. Expand understanding of similar figures and which attributes change and which stay the same: </p>",
            "<ul><li>corresponding angles of two similar figures are the same measure while angles of non-similar figures may not be.</li><li>corresponding side length of the rep-tile (similar figure) increases by the scale factor used to create a new figure. </li><li>perimeter of the rep-tile (similar) figure increases by the scale factor </li><li>area of the rep-tile (similar) figure increases by the scale factor squared. </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
